WEBVTT

00:08.217 --> 00:09.051
[yelling]

00:09.135 --> 00:10.261
[tense music playing]

00:10.344 --> 00:12.138
This is my son. Your grandson.

00:12.221 --> 00:14.306
[Soldier Boy] You're
a fucking disappointment.

00:14.390 --> 00:15.933
-[groaning]
-Get out of the building! Now!

00:16.015 --> 00:17.977
-Butcher, stop!
-[yelling]

00:18.060 --> 00:19.687
[Soldier Boy] Everything you wanted.
He's right fucking there.

00:19.770 --> 00:20.730
And now you blink?

00:20.813 --> 00:21.856
[aide] Ladies and gentlemen,

00:21.939 --> 00:23.816
-the vice president of the United States.
-[groans]

00:23.899 --> 00:25.901
I know exactly what you're thinking.
Literally.

00:25.985 --> 00:27.903
[Sage] Homelander wants
more Starlighters arrested.

00:27.987 --> 00:29.029
As long as you're useful,

00:29.113 --> 00:30.364
everything will come up Ashley.

00:30.448 --> 00:32.950
-Oh, my God, Sameer.
-Is that Zoe's dad?

00:35.327 --> 00:37.496
[Butcher] You're gonna make us
some more of that virus.

00:37.830 --> 00:38.748
-[yelling]
-[Frenchie] Kimiko!

00:38.831 --> 00:40.082
[Annie] You're still working on the virus,

00:40.166 --> 00:42.376
and you want Frenchie.

00:42.460 --> 00:43.544
Homelander's fuming.

00:43.627 --> 00:44.795
He's gonna execute

00:44.879 --> 00:47.423
Hughie, Frenchie, and M in about 36 hours.

00:47.506 --> 00:48.507
We need your help to break them out.

00:48.591 --> 00:49.925
You're fucking crazy.

00:51.469 --> 00:52.636
Mon coeur.

00:52.720 --> 00:53.596
Frenchie.

00:58.601 --> 01:00.060
[grunting]

01:00.144 --> 01:01.479
What was I so afraid of?

01:02.021 --> 01:03.230
[laughing]

01:03.314 --> 01:04.397
-[growls]
-[bones crunch]

01:07.318 --> 01:11.614
-♪ Faster than the speed of light ♪
-[rhythmic clapping]

01:11.697 --> 01:15.159
♪ Watching as your dreams take flight ♪

01:15.242 --> 01:20.372
♪ I think I should stand and fight ♪

01:20.456 --> 01:23.250
♪ Then disappear into the night ♪

01:23.334 --> 01:25.503
♪ Into the night ♪♪

01:25.586 --> 01:28.214
-Praise the Lord.
-[audience member] Praise the Lord.

01:28.297 --> 01:30.758
[others] Praise the Lord.

01:32.343 --> 01:34.220
We come together to mourn

01:34.303 --> 01:37.014
-the one and only A-Train.
-[others] Amen.

01:37.097 --> 01:39.308
[Oh Father] He loved his country,

01:39.390 --> 01:42.019
his God,

01:42.102 --> 01:43.896
but, most of all, his captain.

01:43.979 --> 01:45.314
Homelander, amen.

01:45.396 --> 01:47.191
-[others] Amen.
-[audience member] Amen, sir.

01:47.274 --> 01:49.193
[Oh Father] But...

01:49.276 --> 01:52.404
our martyred brother in Christ...

01:53.531 --> 01:55.199
...was struck down...

01:56.200 --> 01:57.618
...by that jezebel.

01:57.701 --> 01:58.702
[booing, murmuring]

01:58.786 --> 02:01.539
That wily emissary of Satan himself,

02:01.622 --> 02:02.832
Starlight.

02:02.915 --> 02:04.667
-[jeering]
-That's right.

02:04.750 --> 02:06.836
Now, you know
that ain't no figure of speech, right?

02:06.919 --> 02:08.503
It ain't no metaphors in this house.

02:08.586 --> 02:13.467
Starlight and her minions
are literally possessed by demons!

02:13.551 --> 02:15.344
They're spewing vomit!

02:15.427 --> 02:16.470
They're eating babies!

02:16.554 --> 02:19.723
They're turning little boys
into little girls with garden shears!

02:19.807 --> 02:21.725
-Lord have mercy!
-[jeering]

02:25.478 --> 02:27.773
But we cast those demons out
of this house.

02:27.857 --> 02:29.024
-Amen!
-We fight

02:29.108 --> 02:30.901
hellfire with holy fire.

02:30.985 --> 02:32.278
-Mm-hmm.
-We fight

02:32.361 --> 02:34.196
-with the ballot box.
-[agreeing]

02:34.280 --> 02:36.906
We fight with the ammo box!

02:36.991 --> 02:38.868
-[agreeing]
-Matthew 10:34!

02:38.951 --> 02:41.662
"I do not come to bring the peace
but a sword!"

02:41.745 --> 02:43.454
You are not here to be blessed!

02:43.539 --> 02:45.958
You are here to do war!

02:46.041 --> 02:47.167
-[cheering]
-Amen!

02:47.251 --> 02:49.003
-Amen!
-Amen!

02:49.086 --> 02:50.713
Amen.

02:50.796 --> 02:53.257
Can you feel the Holy Ghost's power?

02:53.340 --> 02:57.511
I said, can you feel
the Holy Ghost's power?

02:57.595 --> 02:58.929
-[agreeing]
-Then I need you to praise him.

02:59.013 --> 03:00.222
-Praise him!
-Praise him.

03:00.306 --> 03:02.641
Praise him for victory.

03:02.725 --> 03:04.894
-Praise him for America.
-[others] Praise him!

03:04.977 --> 03:07.563
[Oh Father] Praise him
for our superheroes.

03:07.646 --> 03:11.734
Hallelujah!

03:11.817 --> 03:13.277
Stand up!

03:13.360 --> 03:16.113
Stand up in the name of Jesus!

03:16.196 --> 03:18.532
[woman] My sweet boy.

03:18.616 --> 03:20.701
[tense music playing]

03:20.784 --> 03:22.328
-[Oh Father] Amen!
-[others] Amen!

03:22.411 --> 03:24.163
-[Oh Father] Amen!
-Amen!

03:24.246 --> 03:26.624
-[Oh Father] Amen!
-[organ music playing]

03:26.707 --> 03:28.709
[mysterious music playing]

03:36.884 --> 03:37.885
[grunts]

03:41.096 --> 03:44.141
Welcome to the outskirts
of Erie, Pennsylvania,

03:44.224 --> 03:45.684
a charming little burg

03:45.768 --> 03:48.646
best known for its staggering amount
of fentanyl overdoses.

03:52.232 --> 03:55.069
-[door closes]
-Oh, and, uh,

03:55.152 --> 03:56.278
when you come in here...

03:57.363 --> 03:59.281
...keep your mouths shut

03:59.365 --> 04:01.659
or I'll do the fucking lot of you.

04:04.036 --> 04:06.664
-[♪ Chumbawamba sings "Tubthumping"]
-♪ I get knocked down but I get up again ♪

04:06.747 --> 04:08.582
♪ You're never gonna keep me down ♪

04:08.666 --> 04:11.627
♪ I get knocked down but I get up again ♪

04:11.710 --> 04:13.337
♪ You're never gonna keep me down ♪

04:13.420 --> 04:15.714
♪ He drinks a whiskey drink,
he drinks a vodka drink ♪

04:15.798 --> 04:18.634
♪ He drinks a lager drink,
he drinks a cider drink ♪

04:18.716 --> 04:21.011
♪ He sings the songs
that remind him of the good times...

04:21.095 --> 04:23.222
-You're still working on the virus.
-[Butcher] Not working.

04:23.305 --> 04:24.390
Sorted.

04:25.391 --> 04:27.643
Thanks to this diamond geezer.

04:27.726 --> 04:29.520
♪ I get knocked down but I get up again ♪

04:29.603 --> 04:31.605
♪ You're never gonna keep me down ♪

04:31.689 --> 04:33.190
-Sameer?
-♪ I get knocked down ♪♪

04:34.024 --> 04:37.319
I found him not long after that bollocks
with Neuman and poor little Zoe.

04:40.030 --> 04:42.700
Well, you lot remember, don't you?

04:42.783 --> 04:45.703
When that cunt Homelander...

04:45.786 --> 04:47.788
brutally murdered them in cold blood.

04:47.871 --> 04:49.081
Poor sods.

04:49.164 --> 04:50.249
Didn't stand a chance.

04:50.332 --> 04:52.167
Sameer.

04:52.251 --> 04:53.794
Hi, I'm Hughie. I was friends with Vicky.

04:53.877 --> 04:55.045
I...

04:58.799 --> 05:00.217
I'm so sorry for your loss.

05:00.300 --> 05:01.635
[Kimiko] Are you an idiot?

05:01.719 --> 05:02.720
He cut off your leg with a hatchet.

05:02.803 --> 05:04.388
And kept me prisoner. So did you.

05:04.471 --> 05:05.431
You shot me with the virus.

05:05.514 --> 05:06.557
Your leg regrew.

05:06.640 --> 05:08.267
[Butcher] All right, all right, listen.

05:08.350 --> 05:11.061
The only thing that matters
is we buried said hatchet

05:11.145 --> 05:13.939
so we could crack on
with the godly work of revenge.

05:14.023 --> 05:17.609
And, good news, Sameer's done it.

05:17.693 --> 05:19.820
As of last week,
that naughty little bug of his

05:19.903 --> 05:22.031
is finally strong enough
to top Homelander.

05:22.114 --> 05:24.074
Well, so we reckon.

05:24.158 --> 05:25.200
We just need a little...

05:25.284 --> 05:26.285
dry run.

05:26.368 --> 05:28.871
[Hughie] This thing kills just Homelander?

05:28.954 --> 05:30.330
Or every Supe?

05:30.414 --> 05:31.415
Don't know.

05:31.498 --> 05:33.375
But we'll have a laugh
finding out, won't we?

05:33.459 --> 05:35.502
Jesus fucking Christ.

05:35.586 --> 05:36.837
Will it infect humans?

05:36.920 --> 05:38.422
Well, you know, we got to test it.

05:38.505 --> 05:40.257
[Frenchie] We're close to Cleveland.

05:40.340 --> 05:43.969
You wish to test it on Rock Hard, non?

05:44.053 --> 05:45.137
I'm glad you're back, mate.

05:45.220 --> 05:46.388
Rock Hard?

05:46.472 --> 05:48.724
A member of Teenage Kix.

05:48.807 --> 05:50.683
Rock Hard is a living mountain.

05:50.768 --> 05:53.062
Nine hundred pounds of walking granite.

05:53.145 --> 05:57.066
Hasn't been seen since his unspeakable
acts at the Lincoln Memorial, non?

05:58.192 --> 06:00.194
Oh, he skull-fucked Lincoln in the ear,

06:00.277 --> 06:02.529
filled it with so much hot cum
it burst out of his mouth.

06:04.490 --> 06:05.491
[Butcher] Which...

06:05.574 --> 06:07.493
makes Rock Hard the perfect lab rat.

06:07.576 --> 06:09.036
Indestructible or nearly,

06:09.119 --> 06:11.246
almost as strong as Homelander,

06:11.330 --> 06:13.415
and no one gives a fuck about him.

06:13.499 --> 06:15.084
So we nip in,

06:15.167 --> 06:17.961
twat him, bring him back here
for a dose of kill juice.

06:18.670 --> 06:20.506
Lemon fucking squeezy.

06:21.465 --> 06:23.383
So...

06:23.467 --> 06:24.760
let's get cracking.

06:25.844 --> 06:30.390
[Firecracker] We got to stop the hate
crimes against Supes before they start.

06:30.474 --> 06:33.060
With President Calhoun's
Freedom To Be Free Act,

06:33.143 --> 06:36.522
local superheroes
can now apprehend Starlighters

06:36.605 --> 06:39.066
before they commit any more violence.

06:39.149 --> 06:41.610
[door opens, closes]

06:42.778 --> 06:44.655
Here you go.

06:44.738 --> 06:46.156
Where'd you get these from?

06:46.240 --> 06:47.783
Just friends. But...

06:47.866 --> 06:49.076
they don't need 'em anymore.

06:51.370 --> 06:52.412
[Hughie] So,

06:52.496 --> 06:53.831
how are we gonna do it?

06:53.914 --> 06:55.707
-Do what?
-Get the virus away from Butcher.

06:55.791 --> 06:57.251
-We kill him.
-No, we're not gonna kill him.

06:57.334 --> 06:59.378
We're not just gonna go along
with this, right?

07:01.630 --> 07:03.966
I'm sorry, do we all have amnesia?

07:04.049 --> 07:05.968
Have we forgotten how fucked Butcher is?

07:06.051 --> 07:08.428
He murdered Vicky
in front of her daughter.

07:08.512 --> 07:12.349
Now he wants to murder every Supe
on the planet, which includes you.

07:12.432 --> 07:14.393
I say we take the virus and we run.

07:14.476 --> 07:15.686
-Or kill him.
-[Annie] Look,

07:15.769 --> 07:20.732
it's 10,000 Supes to save
eight billion people worldwide.

07:20.816 --> 07:23.110
That's a good price in any war.

07:24.361 --> 07:25.904
[Mother's Milk] Look, kid.

07:25.988 --> 07:28.157
It's a shit decision, all right?
We're not denying that.

07:28.240 --> 07:30.784
But they're out there
wrangling people up as we speak.

07:30.868 --> 07:32.452
-We don't have a motherfucking choice.
-[Kimiko] Yes,

07:32.536 --> 07:34.288
there is a choice,
and, no, it's not yours to make.

07:34.371 --> 07:36.039
You're not the one who's going to die.

07:36.123 --> 07:37.207
Right?

07:39.668 --> 07:41.336
Why do you always give in to them?

07:41.420 --> 07:42.462
[sighs]

07:43.463 --> 07:44.798
Kimiko, please.

07:44.882 --> 07:46.216
Wait!

07:46.300 --> 07:48.385
[door opens, closes]

07:52.973 --> 07:54.057
[clicks tongue]

07:54.141 --> 07:55.350
[grunts]

07:55.433 --> 07:56.768
[door opens]

07:56.852 --> 07:58.604
[door closes]

07:58.687 --> 07:59.813
Hey.

07:59.897 --> 08:01.481
So...

08:01.565 --> 08:03.525
it's been a tough year. [chuckles softly]

08:03.609 --> 08:04.776
No. No.

08:04.860 --> 08:06.570
I mean, I have been at Epcot, mostly.

08:06.653 --> 08:07.654
Huh.

08:07.738 --> 08:09.531
Why do you bring it up?

08:09.615 --> 08:11.283
Just your whole vibe.

08:11.366 --> 08:12.784
Ditching Ivy and I at the camp.

08:12.868 --> 08:14.745
You're siding with Butcher.
Your hair's different.

08:15.746 --> 08:17.289
Okay, not so much about the hair.

08:17.372 --> 08:18.832
It's just, uh...

08:21.126 --> 08:22.544
[sighs]

08:24.004 --> 08:25.214
Annie,

08:25.297 --> 08:26.840
whatever you had to do...

08:28.091 --> 08:29.092
...I get it.

08:29.176 --> 08:30.761
It's okay.

08:30.844 --> 08:32.346
We can...

08:33.347 --> 08:34.640
We can figure this out.

08:35.724 --> 08:37.601
-We can...
-Talk?

08:37.683 --> 08:39.061
Yeah.

08:39.144 --> 08:40.145
Mm-hmm.

08:40.229 --> 08:41.230
Or...

08:42.313 --> 08:43.398
...counterpoint...

08:44.483 --> 08:46.443
...not talk.

08:46.526 --> 08:47.611
I mean...

08:48.612 --> 08:49.905
Yeah, that's a...

08:49.988 --> 08:52.115
that's a pretty compelling point.

08:52.199 --> 08:53.575
[Annie] Mmm.

08:53.659 --> 08:55.994
[both moaning]

08:59.039 --> 09:01.208
[both moaning]

09:02.626 --> 09:04.836
-[door slams]
-[panting]

09:07.089 --> 09:08.257
You stood there.

09:08.340 --> 09:09.341
Mon coeur, listen--

09:09.424 --> 09:11.718
Chewed off. Sliced in two by Homelander.

09:11.802 --> 09:12.844
Shot here, here, here.

09:12.928 --> 09:14.721
It hurt every time. But the virus?

09:14.805 --> 09:16.807
That was the only time I wanted to die!

09:16.890 --> 09:17.933
The pain.

09:18.308 --> 09:20.143
Agony! Fucking agony!

09:20.227 --> 09:21.979
Butcher's going to do that to me.

09:22.062 --> 09:23.438
And you're okay with it!

09:23.522 --> 09:24.523
No.

09:26.566 --> 09:28.902
On my life, I'm not.

09:28.986 --> 09:30.779
But this is happening

09:30.862 --> 09:33.073
with or without us.

09:33.156 --> 09:37.869
So I must learn everything I can
about this pestilence,

09:37.953 --> 09:40.372
so I can protect you.

09:40.455 --> 09:42.040
[gentle music playing]

09:42.124 --> 09:45.335
I spent every day of the last year...

09:46.586 --> 09:48.547
...dreaming about you.

09:51.925 --> 09:53.468
[speaking French]
Of your hair,

09:53.552 --> 09:55.804
[breathing heavily]

09:55.887 --> 09:57.681
your soft skin,

10:00.600 --> 10:01.893
I dream.

10:04.146 --> 10:08.150
You think that I would let anything...

10:09.234 --> 10:11.695
...take you away from me again?

10:13.613 --> 10:15.324
I dreamt about you, too.

10:15.407 --> 10:16.658
[shuddering]

10:16.742 --> 10:19.202
C'est incroyable.

10:20.746 --> 10:24.333
Your voice is even more beautiful
than I dreamed.

10:24.416 --> 10:26.418
♪ ♪

10:32.883 --> 10:34.718
[both moaning]

10:34.801 --> 10:36.178
Clothes off. Now.

10:36.261 --> 10:38.263
-[♪ INXS sings "Never Tear Us Apart"]
-[panting]

10:41.641 --> 10:43.185
Mwah.

10:45.145 --> 10:46.772
Your bottom half,

10:46.855 --> 10:48.231
is it fully regrown?

10:48.315 --> 10:50.984
My vagina's tingly and damp.

10:51.068 --> 10:52.235
♪ Don't ask me ♪

10:52.319 --> 10:55.489
♪ what you know is true ♪

10:55.572 --> 10:57.574
♪ Don't have to tell you ♪

10:57.657 --> 11:01.578
♪ I love your precious heart ♪

11:01.661 --> 11:03.205
♪ I ♪

11:03.288 --> 11:04.373
[panting]

11:04.456 --> 11:07.000
♪ I was standing ♪

11:08.502 --> 11:10.087
♪ You were there ♪

11:11.671 --> 11:16.385
♪ And they could never tear us apart ♪

11:19.596 --> 11:21.014
♪ I told you ♪

11:23.016 --> 11:25.394
♪ that we could fly ♪

11:26.853 --> 11:30.732
-♪ But some of us don't know why ♪
-[moaning]

11:30.816 --> 11:32.734
[panting]

11:33.985 --> 11:36.238
♪ I was standing ♪

11:37.239 --> 11:38.949
♪ You were there ♪

11:39.032 --> 11:41.201
[moans]

11:41.284 --> 11:43.703
♪ And they could never ever ♪

11:43.787 --> 11:46.748
♪ tear us apart ♪♪

11:51.420 --> 11:53.046
[eerie music playing]

11:55.674 --> 11:57.008
[sighs]

11:59.094 --> 12:00.554
God...

12:00.637 --> 12:02.722
damn it, A-Train.

12:04.891 --> 12:06.017
[sighs]

12:06.101 --> 12:08.562
It didn't need to come to this.

12:08.645 --> 12:09.855
I don't know.

12:09.938 --> 12:12.149
You left me no choice.

12:12.232 --> 12:14.776
I know my leadership style can be...

12:14.860 --> 12:16.361
stern.

12:16.445 --> 12:17.946
But...

12:18.029 --> 12:19.990
it was for your own good.

12:21.741 --> 12:24.286
I liked to think of myself as...

12:24.369 --> 12:25.954
the big brother...

12:27.289 --> 12:29.332
...that you never had.

12:34.629 --> 12:37.883
You remember that girlfriend you had?

12:37.966 --> 12:39.134
Uh...

12:39.217 --> 12:40.218
[sniffles]

12:40.302 --> 12:42.137
Pop...

12:42.220 --> 12:44.097
Popfang.

12:44.181 --> 12:45.557
Betrayed us both.

12:45.640 --> 12:47.517
To William Butcher, no less.

12:47.601 --> 12:49.603
Huge mess. Your fault. What did I do?

12:50.729 --> 12:52.898
What did I do?

12:52.981 --> 12:55.400
I gave you a chance to make things right.

12:55.484 --> 12:58.528
I-I reached out my hand.

13:00.155 --> 13:02.157
And you bit it.

13:02.240 --> 13:04.242
What did I ever do

13:04.326 --> 13:05.744
to deserve that?

13:05.827 --> 13:08.955
What, was I too nurturing?

13:09.039 --> 13:10.499
Too forgiving? Well, maybe.

13:10.582 --> 13:11.791
But, damn it,

13:11.875 --> 13:13.960
you weren't like the others.

13:14.044 --> 13:15.504
Snakes,

13:15.587 --> 13:17.172
backstabbers.

13:17.255 --> 13:18.548
I could count on you, man.

13:18.632 --> 13:20.133
I did count on you.

13:20.217 --> 13:21.593
I loved you.

13:23.678 --> 13:25.597
But here we are.

13:26.681 --> 13:28.600
Why does this keep happening to me?

13:34.523 --> 13:37.359
I guess the strongest men
are the most alone.

13:39.194 --> 13:40.987
You wouldn't understand.

13:43.573 --> 13:45.242
Nobody does.

13:48.620 --> 13:50.622
[pensive music playing]

13:55.335 --> 13:57.337
♪ ♪

14:14.729 --> 14:17.107
[hissing]

14:25.323 --> 14:27.534
♪ Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah ♪

14:27.617 --> 14:29.160
-♪ Ooh ♪
-♪ E-Eyes on me ♪

14:29.244 --> 14:30.287
♪ Pretty when I wake ♪

14:30.370 --> 14:32.622
♪ And I know you want, I know you want,
I know you want more ♪♪

14:32.706 --> 14:34.708
Firecracker's Flaming Freedom Sticks.

14:34.790 --> 14:36.585
I'm Countess Crow:

14:36.668 --> 14:38.461
Countess of the Crows.

14:38.545 --> 14:39.546
And we're doing

14:39.629 --> 14:42.173
a Voughtality vamp glam tutorial.

14:42.257 --> 14:43.341
[Butcher] Wankers.

14:43.425 --> 14:45.802
Can't even take a shit
without it being sponsored.

14:45.885 --> 14:48.346
You know they get paid, like,
50 grand a post for this shit.

14:48.930 --> 14:50.724
-Fifty grand?
-Mm-hmm.

14:51.808 --> 14:52.976
[Butcher] Dog wankers.

14:53.059 --> 14:55.270
