50:08.631 --> 50:10.591
You should've left with A-Train
when he asked you to.

50:10.675 --> 50:13.928
-At least he had a shred of decency.
-That's why he's dead.

50:14.011 --> 50:16.097
"First they came for the Communists,
and I did not speak out

50:16.180 --> 50:17.932
because I was not a Communist."

50:18.015 --> 50:19.600
I don't need Martin Niemöller right now.

50:19.684 --> 50:21.144
You used to love his poetry.

50:21.227 --> 50:23.730
And Birkenstocks and throwing clay.

50:23.813 --> 50:26.065
You used to want to do some good
in the world.

50:26.149 --> 50:29.694
-What happened?
-I tried. I tried.

50:29.777 --> 50:31.320
But there's nothing I can do.

50:31.404 --> 50:34.240
Half of Washington
thinks Homelander's batshit.

50:34.323 --> 50:36.534
The CIA, the Pentagon.

50:36.617 --> 50:38.619
They will follow you if you lead them.

50:38.703 --> 50:41.080
I'm not a leader, I'm vice president.

50:41.164 --> 50:42.790
You can still do some good, Ashley.

50:42.874 --> 50:44.584
We can still do some good.

50:44.667 --> 50:46.377
Just shut up,

50:46.461 --> 50:49.922
or I'm gonna float on my back
in the tub again. You want that?

50:50.006 --> 50:52.383
You're better than this.
You are better than this.

50:52.467 --> 50:54.051
No!

50:55.094 --> 50:56.095
Ow!

50:56.179 --> 50:58.097
[Hughie] So we're clear?

50:58.181 --> 50:59.474
You're absolutely sure?

50:59.557 --> 51:01.851
Triple-checked the results.
None of you are carriers.

51:01.934 --> 51:03.394
Humans are immune.

51:03.478 --> 51:05.897
Une chance. Merci la bonne mère.

51:05.980 --> 51:07.190
[grunts]

51:15.072 --> 51:17.658
[groaning in pain]

51:17.742 --> 51:19.035
[Mother's Milk] Goddamn.

51:19.118 --> 51:21.621
I only seen shit like this one other time.

51:23.289 --> 51:27.752
It was on you outside of that truck stop
whore house on I-23. [laughs]

51:27.835 --> 51:30.880
[Butcher] Soldier Cunt down.
Homelander to go.

51:30.963 --> 51:33.549
-We fucking did it.
-About time.

51:34.550 --> 51:36.344
[door opens]

51:37.804 --> 51:38.888
Mon coeur.

51:40.097 --> 51:42.558
[gentle music playing]

51:46.604 --> 51:48.314
Let's run away.

51:50.233 --> 51:51.234
What?

51:51.317 --> 51:55.696
There are over 50 uninhabited islands
in the Pacific.

51:55.780 --> 52:00.743
We just need to find one so remote,
nobody will ever find us.

52:02.787 --> 52:04.664
You were right.

52:04.747 --> 52:09.293
This virus,
there is no containing it, no stopping it.

52:09.377 --> 52:12.046
I do not know how to protect you from it,

52:12.129 --> 52:16.634
except to take you as far away
from here as possible.

52:26.060 --> 52:30.231
We have to stay.

52:32.108 --> 52:36.279
Mon amour, you did not see its carnage.

52:36.362 --> 52:38.865
-It's too dangerous.
-It's dangerous for everyone now.

52:38.948 --> 52:40.992
Innocent people are being round up.

52:41.075 --> 52:43.744
No. Je peux pas.

52:43.828 --> 52:46.414
Don't ask me to watch you die.

52:46.497 --> 52:48.833
I think this is how we make amends.

52:50.418 --> 52:52.837
For the lives we've taken.
I think we have to...

52:54.255 --> 52:56.591
Get up every day and keep going?

52:56.674 --> 52:58.426
[somber music playing]

53:01.971 --> 53:03.097
Oui.

53:08.102 --> 53:09.478
C'est ça.

53:12.106 --> 53:13.816
[vape hissing]

53:25.745 --> 53:27.455
You're allowed to freak out, you know.

53:27.538 --> 53:29.206
This virus.

53:31.042 --> 53:32.543
It's fucking brutal.

53:32.627 --> 53:36.839
I don't know, for Rock Hard,
I'd say it's an improvement.

53:39.634 --> 53:42.219
I haven't exactly had
a magical year either.

53:42.303 --> 53:44.138
Neither of us is fine.

53:45.806 --> 53:47.558
And we shouldn't be.

53:47.642 --> 53:49.602
And if you don't want to talk about it,

53:49.685 --> 53:51.562
-you don't have to.
-Perfect.

53:51.646 --> 53:53.606
But I'm not letting you die.

53:56.484 --> 53:58.110
I'm gonna keep fighting.

54:00.821 --> 54:04.533
And if you can't,
then I'm just gonna fight for both of us.

54:06.327 --> 54:10.081
But just don't turn into
fucking Butcher, okay?

54:10.164 --> 54:12.166
[slow, dramatic music playing]

54:21.300 --> 54:22.426
[door opens]

54:26.347 --> 54:29.600
I know. I'm late.

54:33.104 --> 54:35.106
[Terror whining softly]

54:43.614 --> 54:45.366
All right, Terror.

54:47.785 --> 54:50.037
Time for your meds.

54:53.833 --> 54:55.334
Oh, yeah.

54:58.087 --> 55:00.965
-Who's a good boy, ay?
-[whines softly]

55:07.096 --> 55:09.432
[spraying]

55:11.976 --> 55:13.477
[booming thud]

55:14.729 --> 55:15.730
Whoa, hey.

55:15.813 --> 55:17.064
Be careful, sir.

55:17.148 --> 55:18.315
There's a viral contagion.

55:18.399 --> 55:21.652
I got here as soon as I heard,
and I locked shit down.

55:21.736 --> 55:25.489
Sending Soldier Boy to test the waters,
pretty fucking strategic, sir.

55:25.573 --> 55:28.659
You're always playing 3D chess,
aren't you?

55:28.743 --> 55:30.494
I told him to report back.

55:30.578 --> 55:33.873
Told him not to go in alone.
Why would he do that?

55:33.956 --> 55:36.292
Well, it's more like Soldier Doy,

55:36.375 --> 55:38.002
-am I right?
-Leave.

55:39.128 --> 55:40.546
Well, I just, um, got to be here, sir.

55:40.629 --> 55:42.214
-To do the--
-Should've been you.

55:42.298 --> 55:43.340
Okay.

55:43.424 --> 55:45.426
-I'm sorry.
-Leave.

55:45.509 --> 55:47.511
[tense music playing]

55:51.432 --> 55:53.350
I was swimming.

55:59.356 --> 56:00.691
[inhales sharply]

56:02.777 --> 56:04.403
[somber music playing]

56:10.659 --> 56:12.119
No...

56:14.705 --> 56:16.415
No...

56:17.958 --> 56:20.002
Not you, too.

56:20.086 --> 56:22.254
Not you.

56:25.216 --> 56:26.509
[grunting]

56:29.970 --> 56:32.473
Why does everyone keep leaving me?

56:35.309 --> 56:38.270
I'm sorry. [sniffles]

56:41.440 --> 56:43.567
[man] Hazardous site.
Stay back.

